original: LAGERGREN, Gösta August, Direktör, Stockholm, f Sthlm 24/11 96 av prof SAL o Jenny Fredriksson, gm Rose Haglund. Studex Sthlm 15. Anst Nord Kreditbkn 15, Sthlms Ensk Bk 16, rembours- o arbitr.avd Industribkn o Gbgs Hdlsbk 17—26, kamr AB Terapeutika 26—30, v. vkst dir där o i ds cftr AB Rila-Terapeutika o AB Tika 30—39, vkst dir sed. 39, vkst dir AB Tikamin sed. 42, styr.led dsa. Resor: Danm, Norge, Estl, Finl, Tyskl, Frankr, Schweiz, Tjeckoslov, Österr, Ung. Idrm, skyttm; Timmermansorden, Pe-larorden. Hobbies: Musik, skönlitteratur, segling, vintersport.
translated: LAGERGREN, Gösta August, Director, Stockholm, b. Stockholm 24/11 96, son of Professor SAL and Jenny Fredriksson, m. Rose Haglund. Graduated Stockholm 15. Employed at Nord Kreditbkn 15, Sthlms Ensk Bk 16, rembours and arbitration department of Industribkn and Gbgs Hdlsbk 17-26, chamberlain at AB Terapeutika 26-30, deputy managing director there and at AB Rila-Terapeutika and AB Tika 30-39, managing director since 39, managing director at AB Tikamin since 42, board member in the same association. Travels: Denmark, Norway, Estonia, Finland, Germany, France, Switzerland, Czechoslovakia, Austria, Hungary. Interests: Music, fiction literature, sailing, winter sports. Memberships: Timberman's Order, Pillar Order.
